page.title: 02BRINGTON, Cambridgeshire
page.content:
Compact village, population 55 adults, 11 under-18s, 29 houses, 2 farms. Just outside survey area is housing associ- ated with RAF Alconbury and Molesworth
Wheatsheaf PH replaced by modern bunga low. Old Rectory, built 1855, now private house. Rector resides in new Rectory built 1971, also has care of Molesworth, Old Weston and Leighton Bromswold parishes.
Area school built 1970. Last shop/Post Office closed 1978. Mobile vans call weekly. Manor Farm has unique trade - grow bird seed + tic beans, sell to Truro; Wales; Inverness; miners from Nottingham for racing pigeons.
Several fields permanent pasture. "Fox Holes" expanse of woodland E of village
